          }}>{`basic Lua concepts`}</a>{`.`}</li>
        <li parentName="ul">{`You understand the `}<a parentName="li" {...{
            "href": "/docs/about/concepts/"
          }}>{`basic Vector concepts`}</a>{` and understand `}<a parentName="li" {...{
            "href": "/guides/getting-started/your-first-pipeline/"
          }}>{`how to set up a pipeline`}</a>{`.`}</li>
      </ul>
    </Assumptions>
    <p>{`Vector has many built-in `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/components/?functions%5B%5D=parse/"
      }}>{`parsers`}</a>{` for structured logs formats. However, when you need to ship
logs in a custom or application-specific format, `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/components/?functions%5B%5D=program/"
      }}>{`programmable transforms`}</a>{` have got you
covered.`}</p>
    <p>{`This guide walks through reading CSV logs using `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/sources/file/"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`file`}</inlineCode></a>{` source and parsing them using
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/transforms/lua/"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`lua`}</inlineCode></a>{` transform with a loadable Lua module.`}</p>
    {
      /*
          THIS FILE IS AUTOGENERATED!
           To make changes please edit the template located at:
           website/guides/advanced/parsing-csv-logs-with-lua.md.erb
      */
    }
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "getting-started"
    }}>{`Getting Started`}</h2>
    <p>{`For certainty, it is assumed in the following that the logs to be read are produced by
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/runtime-config-logging.html#RUNTIME-CONFIG-LOGGING-CSVLOG"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`csvlog`}</inlineCode></a>{` in PostgreSQL. For example, there might be the following
log file:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-csv",
        "metastring": "title=\"log.csv\"",
        "title": "\"log.csv\""
      }}>{`2020-04-09 12:48:49.661 UTC,,,1,,localhost.1,1,,2020-04-09 12:48:49 UTC,,0,LOG,00000,"ending log output to stderr",,"Future log output will go to log destination ""csvlog"".",,,,,,,""
2020-04-09 12:48:49.669 UTC,,,27,,localhost.1b,1,,2020-04-09 12:48:49 UTC,,0,LOG,00000,"database system was shut down at 2020-04-09 12:48:25 UTC",,,,,,,,,""
2020-04-09 12:48:49.683 UTC,,,1,,localhost.1,2,,2020-04-09 12:48:49 UTC,,0,LOG,00000,"database system is ready to accept connections",,,,,,,,,""
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Let us draft an initial version of the Vector's configuration file:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-toml",
        "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
        "title": "\"vector.toml\""
      }}>{`data_dir = "."

[sources.file]
  type = "file"
  include = ["*.csv"]
  start_at_beginning = true

[transforms.lua]
  inputs = ["file"]
  type = "lua"
  version = "2"
  hooks.process = """
    function (event, emit)
      -- to be expanded
      emit(event)
    end
  """

[sinks.console]
  inputs = ["lua"]
  type = "console"
  encoding = "json"
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`This config sets up a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/meta/glossary/#pipeline"
      }}>{`pipeline`}</a>{` that reads log files, pipes them through the parsing
transform (which currently is configured to just pass the events through), and displays the produced log events using
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/sinks/console/"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`console`}</inlineCode></a>{` sink.`}</p>
    <p>{`At this point, running `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`vector --config vector.toml`}</inlineCode>{` results in the following output:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-json"
      }}>{`{"file":"log.csv","host":"localhost","message":"2020-04-09 12:48:49.661 UTC,,,1,,localhost.1,1,,2020-04-09 12:48:49 UTC,,0,LOG,00000,\\"ending log output to stderr\\",,\\"Future log output will go to log destination \\"\\"csvlog\\"\\".\\",,,,,,,\\"\\"","timestamp":"2020-04-09T14:33:28Z"}
{"file":"log.csv","host":"localhost","message":"2020-04-09 12:48:49.669 UTC,,,27,,localhost.1b,1,,2020-04-09 12:48:49 UTC,,0,LOG,00000,\\"database system was shut down at 2020-04-09 12:48:25 UTC\\",,,,,,,,,\\"\\"","timestamp":"2020-04-09T14:33:28Z"}
{"file":"log.csv","host":"localhost","message":"2020-04-09 12:48:49.683 UTC,,,1,,localhost.1,2,,2020-04-09 12:48:49 UTC,,0,LOG,00000,\\"database system is ready to accept connections\\",,,,,,,,,\\"\\"","timestamp":"2020-04-09T14:33:28Z"}
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "adding-the-csv-module"
    }}>{`Adding the CSV Module`}</h2>
    <p>{`In order to perform actual parsing, it is possible to leverage `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/geoffleyland/lua-csv"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`lua-csv`}</inlineCode></a>{`.
Because it consists of a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/geoffleyland/lua-csv/blob/09557e4608b02d136b9ae39a8fa0f36328fa1cec/lua/csv.lua"
      }}>{`single file`}</a>{`, it is possible to just download it to the same
directory where `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`vector.toml`}</inlineCode>{` is stored:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`curl -o csv.lua https://raw.githubusercontent.com/geoffleyland/lua-csv/d20cd42d61dc52e7f6bcb13b596ac7a7d4282fbf/lua/csv.lua
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Then it would be possible to load it by calling `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://www.lua.org/manual/5.3/manual.html#pdf-require"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`require`}</inlineCode></a>{` Lua function in the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/transforms/lua/#source"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`source`}</inlineCode></a>{` configuration section:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-toml"
      }}>{`source = """
  csv = require("csv")
"""
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`With this `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`source`}</inlineCode>{` the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`csv`}</inlineCode>{` module is loaded when Vector is started up (or if the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`lua`}</inlineCode>{` transform is added later and the
config is `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/administration/process-management/#automatic-reload-on-changes"
      }}>{`automatically reloaded`}</a>{`) and can
be used through the global variable `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`csv`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "implementing-custom-parsing"
    }}>{`Implementing Custom Parsing`}</h2>
    <p>{`With the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`csv`}</inlineCode>{` module, the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/transforms/lua/#process"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`hooks.process`}</inlineCode></a>{` can be changed to the following:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-toml"
      }}>{`hooks.process = """
  function (event, emit)
    fields = csv.openstring(event.log.message):lines()() -- parse the \`message\` field
    event.log.message = nil -- drop the \`message\` field

    column_names = {  -- a sequence containing CSV column names
      -- ...
    }

    for column, value in ipairs(fields) do -- iterate over CSV columns
      column_name = column_names[column] -- get column name
      event.log[column_name] = value -- set the corresponding field in the event
    end

    emit(event) -- emit the transformed event
  end
"""
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Note that the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`column_names`}</inlineCode>{` can be created just once, in the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`source`}</inlineCode>{` section instead to speed up processing.
Putting it there and using the column names from the PostgreSQL documentation results in the following definition of
the whole transform:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-toml",
        "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
        "title": "\"vector.toml\""
      }}>{`# ...
[transforms.lua]
  inputs = ["file"]
  type = "lua"
  version = "2"
  source = """
    csv = require("csv") -- load external module for parsing CSV
    column_names = {  -- a sequence containing CSV column names
      "log_time",
      "user_name",
      "database_name",
      "process_id",
      "connection_from",
      "session_id",
      "session_line_num",
      "command_tag",
      "session_start_time",
      "virtual_transaction_id",
      "transaction_id",
      "error_severity",
      "sql_state_code",
      "message",
      "detail",
      "hint",
      "internal_query",
      "internal_query_pos",
      "context",
      "query",
      "query_pos",
      "location",
      "application_name",
    }
  """
  hooks.process = """
    function (event, emit)
      fields = csv.openstring(event.log.message):lines()() -- parse the \`message\` field
      event.log.message = nil -- drop the \`message\` field

      for column, value in ipairs(fields) do -- iterate over CSV columns
        column_name = column_names[column] -- get column name
        event.log[column_name] = value -- set the corresponding field in the event
      end

      emit(event) -- emit the transformed event
    end
    """
#...
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Trying to run `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`vector --config vector.toml`}</inlineCode>{` with the same input file results in structured events being output:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-json"
      }}>{`{"application_name":"","command_tag":"","connection_from":"","context":"","database_name":"","detail":"","error_severity":"LOG","file":"log.csv","hint":"Future log output will go to log destination \\"csvlog\\".","host":"localhost","internal_query":"","internal_query_pos":"","location":"","log_time":"2020-04-09 12:48:49.661 UTC","message":"ending log output to stderr","process_id":"1","query":"","query_pos":"","session_id":"localhost.1","session_line_num":"1","session_start_time":"2020-04-09 12:48:49 UTC","sql_state_code":"00000","timestamp":"2020-04-09T19:49:07Z","transaction_id":"0","user_name":"","virtual_transaction_id":""}
{"application_name":"","command_tag":"","connection_from":"","context":"","database_name":"","detail":"","error_severity":"LOG","file":"log.csv","hint":"","host":"localhost","internal_query":"","internal_query_pos":"","location":"","log_time":"2020-04-09 12:48:49.669 UTC","message":"database system was shut down at 2020-04-09 12:48:25 UTC","process_id":"27","query":"","query_pos":"","session_id":"localhost.1b","session_line_num":"1","session_start_time":"2020-04-09 12:48:49 UTC","sql_state_code":"00000","timestamp":"2020-04-09T19:49:07Z","transaction_id":"0","user_name":"","virtual_transaction_id":""}
{"application_name":"","command_tag":"","connection_from":"","context":"","database_name":"","detail":"","error_severity":"LOG","file":"log.csv","hint":"","host":"localhost","internal_query":"","internal_query_pos":"","location":"","log_time":"2020-04-09 12:48:49.683 UTC","message":"database system is ready to accept connections","process_id":"1","query":"","query_pos":"","session_id":"localhost.1","session_line_num":"2","session_start_time":"2020-04-09 12:48:49 UTC","sql_state_code":"00000","timestamp":"2020-04-09T19:49:07Z","transaction_id":"0","user_name":"","virtual_transaction_id":""}
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Or, applying pretty formatting to one of the output events:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-json"
      }}>{`{
  "application_name": "",
  "command_tag": "",
  "connection_from": "",
  "context": "",
  "database_name": "",
  "detail": "",
  "error_severity": "LOG",
  "file": "log.csv",
  "hint": "Future log output will go to log destination \\"csvlog\\".",
  "host": "localhost",
  "internal_query": "",
  "internal_query_pos": "",
  "location": "",
  "log_time": "2020-04-09 12:48:49.661 UTC",
  "message": "ending log output to stderr",
  "process_id": "1",
  "query": "",
  "query_pos": "",
  "session_id": "localhost.1",
  "session_line_num": "1",
  "session_start_time": "2020-04-09 12:48:49 UTC",
  "sql_state_code": "00000",
  "timestamp": "2020-04-09T19:49:07Z",
  "transaction_id": "0",
  "user_name": "",
  "virtual_transaction_id": ""
}
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "further-improvements"
    }}>{`Further Improvements`}</h2>
    <p>{`After the task of parsing the CSV logs is accomplished, the following improvements can take place.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "support-for-multi-line-strings"
    }}>{`Support for Multi-line Strings`}</h3>
    <p>{`CSV supports line breaks in strings. However, by default `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`file`}</inlineCode>{` source creates a separate event from each line.`}</p>
    <p>{`There are two options to deal with this:`}</p>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`For simple cases it might be possible to use the `}<a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "/docs/reference/sources/file/#multiline"
        }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`multiline`}</inlineCode></a>{` configuration
option in the `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`file`}</inlineCode>{` source.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`For more complex cases the messages from multiple events can be conditionally concatenated in the Lua code. See
`}<a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "/guides/advanced/custom-aggregations-with-lua/"
        }}>{`the aggregations guide`}</a>{` for more details on this.`}</li>
    </ol>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "change-fields-types"
    }}>{`Change Fields Types`}</h3>
    <p>{`By default, all columns are parsed as strings. It is possible to convert them to other
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/transforms/lua/#data-types"
      }}>{`data types`}</a>{` right in the Lua code using
built-in functions, such as `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://www.lua.org/manual/5.3/manual.html#pdf-tonumber"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`tonumber`}</inlineCode></a>{`. Alternatively, it is possible to add the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/transforms/coercer/"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`coercer`}</inlineCode></a>{` transform after the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`lua`}</inlineCode>{` transform, for example, to
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/transforms/coercer/#timestamps"
      }}>{`parse timestamps`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

